title: Process only the latest file, once
content:
#! /bin/bash
# Set cron to run this periodically

# Find the latest file, assuming easily sortable
TARGET=/home/lucas.hartmann/Documentos/cpp/growatt/data
FILE="$(find "$TARGET" -maxdepth 1 -iname *.json | sort | tail -n1)"

# Abort if latest file has already been worked on
STATEFILE=/tmp/statefile
touch $STATEFILE
[ "$FILE" == "$(cat $STATEFILE)" ] && exit 0
echo "$FILE" > $STATEFILE

# Do your thing here
echo "Work on $FILE..."

title: MAXMATCH - Maximum Self-Matching
[Roblox] - Tadachii's Flag Wars - [Remove All Dirt Script]
content:
--This script removes all dirt in the game "Flag Wars"

-- Function to recursively find and delete BaseParts named "dirt"
local function deleteDirt(parts)
    for _, part in ipairs(parts) do
        if part:IsA("BasePart") and part.Name == "dirt" then
            part:Destroy()
        elseif part:IsA("Model") then
            deleteDirt(part:GetChildren())
        end
    end
end

-- Call the function on all BaseParts in the game
local function deleteAllDirt()
    deleteDirt(game.Workspace:GetDescendants())
end

-- Call the function to start the deletion process
deleteAllDirt()

--@name Holodraw Example
--@author Name
--@client

local function reset()
    render.setStencilWriteMask(0xFF)
    render.setStencilTestMask(0xFF)
    render.setStencilReferenceValue(0)
    render.setStencilCompareFunction(STENCIL.ALWAYS)
    render.setStencilPassOperation(STENCIL.KEEP)
    render.setStencilFailOperation(STENCIL.KEEP)
    render.setStencilZFailOperation(STENCIL.KEEP)
    render.clearStencil()
end

local function mask(mask, target, invert)
    reset()
    render.setStencilEnable(true)
    render.setStencilReferenceValue(1)
    render.setStencilCompareFunction(1)
    render.setStencilFailOperation(3)
        mask()
    render.setStencilCompareFunction(invert and 6 or 3)
    render.setStencilFailOperation(1)
        target()
    render.setStencilEnable(false)
end

local pi, cos, sin = math.pi, math.cos, math.sin
local function get_rounded_poly(x, y, w, h, r, f)
    local poly = {}
    local f2 = f*2

    for i = f * 0, f * 1 do local rad = i / f2 * pi; poly[#poly + 1] = { x = x + r     - cos(rad) * r, y = y + r     - sin(rad) * r } end
    for i = f * 1, f * 2 do local rad = i / f2 * pi; poly[#poly + 1] = { x = x + w - r - cos(rad) * r, y = y + r     - sin(rad) * r } end
    for i = f * 2, f * 3 do local rad = i / f2 * pi; poly[#poly + 1] = { x = x + w - r - cos(rad) * r, y = y + h - r - sin(rad) * r } end
    for i = f * 3, f * 4 do local rad = i / f2 * pi; poly[#poly + 1] = { x = x + r     - cos(rad) * r, y = y + h - r - sin(rad) * r } end

    return poly
end

-------------------------------------------

local rounded_rect = get_rounded_poly(0, 0, 100, 100, 16, 4)

render.createRenderTarget("canvas")
hook.add("render", "", function()
    
    render.selectRenderTarget("canvas")
    
    mask(function()
        render.drawPoly(rounded_rect)
    end,
    function()
        render.setColor(Color(20, 160, 240))
        render.drawRect(0, 0, 1024, 1024)
    end)
    
    render.selectRenderTarget()
    
    
    render.setColor(Color(255, 255, 255))
    render.setRenderTargetTexture("canvas")
    render.drawTexturedRect(0, 0, 512, 512)
end)

```python
from langchain.chat_models import ChatOpenAI
from langchain.chains import LLMChain, SequentialChain
from langchain.memory import ConversationBufferMemory
from langchain.prompts import PromptTemplate

llm = ChatOpenAI(temperature=0.7,)
memory = ConversationBufferMemory(memory_key="chat_history", input_key="human_input")

system_template = """You are a writer who is well-versed in the writing styles of children's book and story authors.

{chat_history}
Human: {human_input}
Writer:"""
system_prompt = PromptTemplate(input_variables=["chat_history", "human_input"], template=system_template)

author_template = """Given an author's name, describe the writing style of the given author.

Author: {author}

Writer: This is a description of the style of the above author:"""
author_prompt = PromptTemplate(input_variables=["author"], template=author_template)
author_chain = LLMChain(llm=llm, prompt=author_prompt, output_key="author_style")

outline_template = """Given an author's name, a description of their writing style, and a child's age, write an outline for an age-appropriate bedtime story in the style of the given author.

Age: {age}
Author: {author}
Author's Style: {author_style}

Writer: This is an outline for a story in the style of the above author:"""
outline_prompt = PromptTemplate(
    input_variables=["age", "author", "author_style"], template=outline_template
)
outline_chain = LLMChain(llm=llm, prompt=outline_prompt, output_key="outline")

story_template = """Given an outline for a children's bedtime story, write an age-appropriate story in the style of the given author.

Age: {age}
Author: {author}
Author's Style: {author_style}
Story Outline: {outline}

Writer: This is an age-appropriate story (for {age} year-olds), based on the above outline, in the style of {author}:"""
story_prompt = PromptTemplate(
    input_variables=["age", "author", "author_style", "outline"],
    template=story_template,
)
story_chain = LLMChain(llm=llm, prompt=story_prompt)

overall_chain = SequentialChain(
    chains=[author_chain, outline_chain, story_chain],
    input_variables=["age", "author"],
    verbose=True,
    memory=memory,
)
review = overall_chain({"age": 6, "author": "Dr. Seuss"})

print(review)
```

local monitor = peripheral.wrap( "right" )
local chartbl = {"*","%","@"}
local colortbl = {colors.blue, colors.lightBlue, colors.cyan, colors.green, colors.lime, colors.yellow, colors.pink, colors.magenta, colors.purple, colors.blue}

local curCol, incCol, reverse, maxx, maxy = 1, 1, false, monitor.getSize()

local function advClear( c, b, t )
	monitor.setBackgroundColor( b )
	monitor.setTextColor( t )
	write( "\n" .. c:rep( maxx ) .. "\n" .. c:rep( maxx ) )
end

monitor.setCursorPos( 1, maxy )

while true do
	for theChar = 1, #chartbl do
		advClear( chartbl[ theChar ], colortbl[ curCol ], colortbl[ curCol + (1) ] or colortbl[ 1 ] )
		sleep( 0.05 )
	end
	for theChar = #chartbl, 1, -1 do
		advClear( chartbl[ theChar ], colortbl[ curCol + (1) ] or colortbl[ 1 ], colortbl[ curCol ]  )
		sleep( 0.05 )
	end
	curCol = curCol + 1
	if curCol == #colortbl then
		curCol = 1
	end
end

# RPi.GPIO is for adjusting and reading the GPIO pins on the Pi
# time.sleep is for pausing and slowing down the code to reduce load and problems
# pyautogui is for simulating mouse movement and clicks (NEEDS TO BE INSTALLED FIRST)
#
import RPi.GPIO as GPIO
from time import sleep
import pyautogui

# remove useless warning
pyautogui.FAILSAFE = False

# these are the pins I used, it's not necessary to use the same exact ones
# i'm using the BCM numbering, NOT the physical positions of the pins on the PCB
# gpio 14 - relay output
# gpio 15, 4, 3, 2 - positions dial 1 (1-4)
# gpio 27, 22, 23, 24, 10, 9 - positions dial 2 (1-6)
relay = 14
dial_mode = [15, 4, 3, 2]
dial_day = [27, 22, 23, 24, 10, 9]

# mouse positions for the different buttons on the webpage
# mx is for the horizontal positions, my is for the vertical position, which is the same for each option in a group
# modes is for off, temp, rain, wind
# days is for monday, tuesday, etc.

mx_modes = [-1, 77, 193, 277]
my_modes = 167
mx_days = [63, 173, 279, 385, 494, 600]
my_days = 421

#current and previous knob position variables, necessary for telling the exact moment the knob has moved

pos_mode = -1
pos_day = -1
pos_mode_prev = -1
pos_day_prev = -1

crt_on = False

# set relay pin to output mode, every other pin to input mode
# the input pins use the built-in pullup resistors, because the knobs
# connect the pins to ground

GPIO.setmode(GPIO.BCM)
GPIO.setup(relay, GPIO.OUT)
GPIO.output(relay, GPIO.LOW)

for i in dial_mode:
    GPIO.setup(i, GPIO.IN, pull_up_down=GPIO.PUD_UP)
for i in dial_day:
    GPIO.setup(i, GPIO.IN, pull_up_down=GPIO.PUD_UP)

# this function below cycles through all the pins responding to knob positions
# and sees which one is selected currently
# it checks "IF NOT" because a pin is activated when it is connected to ground, i.e. LOW
# and all the others are pulled up by default, so - HIGH

def update_dials():
    global pos_mode
    global pos_day
    for i, gp in enumerate(dial_mode):
        if not GPIO.input(gp):
            pos_mode = i

    for i, gp in enumerate(dial_day):
        if not GPIO.input(gp):
            pos_day = i

# this function checks if the CRT is off and turns it on

def activate():
    global crt_on
    global relay
    if not crt_on:
        GPIO.output(relay, GPIO.HIGH)
        crt_on = True

# initial adjustments

update_dials()
pos_mode_prev = pos_mode
pos_day_prev = pos_day

# begin main loop

try:
    while True:

        update_dials()
        # if a knob position has changed
        if pos_mode != pos_mode_prev:
            # this loop below makes sure that 0.2 seconds pass since the knob has last changed
            # before it starts doing anything
            # this is so that if you move it quickly through a bunch of positions
            # it doesn't simulate a bunch of mouse clicks quickly and screw something up in the browser
            while True:
                pos_mode_prev = pos_mode
                sleep(0.2)
                update_dials()
                # if after 0.2 seconds nothing has changed
                if pos_mode == pos_mode_prev:
                    # if the mode knob wasn't just set to OFF position, move mouse to the appropriate
                    # position on the screen, then wait 10ms and click left button
                    # the activate function is called so that if the previous position was OFF, the CRT should now turn on
                    if pos_mode != 0:
                        pyautogui.moveTo(mx_modes[pos_mode], my_modes)
                        sleep(0.01)
                        pyautogui.click()
                        activate()
                    else:
                        # if the knob was just set to the OFF position, turn the CRT off
                        GPIO.output(relay, GPIO.LOW)
                        crt_on = False
                    break
        # now perform the same checks for the other knob (without the CRT power state because this knob doesn't affect it)
        if pos_day != pos_day_prev:
            while True:
                pos_day_prev = pos_day
                sleep(0.2)
                update_dials()
                if pos_day == pos_day_prev:
                    pyautogui.moveTo(mx_days[pos_day], my_days)
                    sleep(0.01)
                    pyautogui.click()
                    break
        # update last known positions before beginning the loop again
        pos_mode_prev = pos_mode
        pos_day_prev = pos_day

        # slow down the code a bit, so that it doesn't overheat the Pi
        sleep(0.02)
finally:
    GPIO.cleanup()

title: Camera Effects Client Script
content:
local cam = game.Workspace.CurrentCamera

local jumpscareTime = 3.5

local remote = game.ReplicatedStorage.cameraEffects


game.Lighting.Atmosphere.Density = 0.03
game.Lighting.ColorCorrection.Brightness = 0

cam.CameraType = Enum.CameraType.Custom
cam.CameraSubject = game.Players.LocalPlayer.Character:WaitForChild("Humanoid")

function addBrightness()
	
	for i = 1, 10, 1 do
		
		game.Lighting.Atmosphere.Density = i/20
		game.Lighting.ColorCorrection.Brightness = i/20
		wait()
	end

end

remote.OnClientEvent:Connect(function()

	repeat
		cam.CameraType = Enum.CameraType.Scriptable
	until    cam.CameraType == Enum.CameraType.Scriptable

	local startTime = tick()

	spawn(addBrightness)
	

	repeat

		wait()
		local  endTime = tick()
		local randX = math.random(-150,150) / 50
		local randY = math.random(-150,150) / 50
		local randZ = math.random(-150,150) / 50

		cam.CFrame = cam.CFrame * CFrame.Angles(math.rad(randX), math.rad(randY), math.rad(randZ))

	until endTime - startTime >= jumpscareTime

	cam.CameraType = Enum.CameraType.Custom
	cam.CameraSubject = game.Players.LocalPlayer.Character:WaitForChild("Humanoid")
	
	wait(4)
	

	game.Lighting.Atmosphere.Density = 0.03
	game.Lighting.ColorCorrection.Brightness = 0
end)

title: Dash regex filter example
content:
import dash
import dash_core_components as dcc
import dash_html_components as html
from dash.dependencies import Input, Output
import plotly.express as px
import re

# Créer un dataframe avec des données aléatoires
df = px.data.gapminder().query("year == 2007")

# Créer une application dash
app = dash.Dash(__name__)

# Définir le layout de l'application
app.layout = html.Div([
    # Un titre
    html.H1("Filtrer les légendes avec une expression regex"),
    # Un graphique plotly
    dcc.Graph(id="graph"),
    # Une text box pour entrer le regex
    html.Div([
        html.Label("Entrez une expression regex:"),
        dcc.Input(id="regex-input", type="text", value=".*")
    ])
])

# Définir une fonction qui met à jour le graphique en fonction du regex
@app.callback(
    Output("graph", "figure"),
    Input("regex-input", "value")
)
def update_graph(regex):
    # Créer un masque booléen pour filtrer les lignes du dataframe qui correspondent au regex
    mask = df["country"].apply(lambda x: bool(re.match(regex, x)))
    # Créer un sous-dataframe avec les lignes filtrées
    filtered_df = df[mask]
    # Créer un graphique plotly avec le sous-dataframe
    fig = px.scatter(filtered_df, x="gdpPercap", y="lifeExp", size="pop", color="continent", hover_name="country", log_x=True, size_max=60)
    # Retourner le graphique
    return fig

# Lancer l'application
app.run(debug=True, renderer='browser')

"3s", "3c", "3d", "3h",
"2s", "2c", "2d", "2h"
}

math.randomseed(os.time())

function shuffle(deck)
    for i = #deck, 2, -1 do
		local j = math.random(i)
		deck[i], deck[j] = deck[j], deck[i]
	end
end



shuffle(deck)

textutils.tabulate(deck)

The dystopian version of superintelligence is illustrated with frequency by leaders in the technology industry, and is famously depicted by Hollywood in films like Terminator, 
or more recently Ex Machina, and even the Avengers. The “furious deity A.I.” is a story you know, because it is the story you are constantly told: we build the thinking machine, 
it surpasses our abilities in every way, and it destroys us for one of any number of reasons.Maybe it perceives us as a threat. Maybe we’re just in its way, 
and it hardly perceives us at all — mankind, a disposable insect race.

There are of course many arguments in opposition to the now ubiquitous concept of our apocalypse by artificial intelligence. 
I myself have called into question the logic of such dystopian arguments in Anatomy of Next. But our subject here is less pertaining to the nature of the conscious machine than 
it is to the way we talk about this subject, and what it means. First, consider that most of the artificial intelligence depicted in culture looks human, a representation with 
no basis in technological reality. Then, the true scope of the Singularity is almost impossible to predict, which begs a question: where are these opinions about the broadly 
unknowable coming from?

select soc.user_id,
       c.payment_type,
       c.flag_card,
       soi.price,
       soi.payment_date,
       soi.send_date,
       sop.payment_type,
       sop.value,
       sop.discount,
       sop.quantity,
       soc.consumed,
       i.cart_item_id,
       i.price,
       i.send_date,
       i.installment,
       ci.last_invoice_status,
       ci.discount_price,
       c.status,
       sop.created_at,
       soi.created_at
from store_oneclick_invoice soi
         join store_oneclick_purchase sop on soi.store_oneclick_purchase_id = sop.id
         join store_oneclick_campaign soc on sop.oneclick_campaign_id = soc.id
         join invoice i on soi.invoice_id = i.id
         join cart_items ci on i.cart_item_id = ci.id
         join cart c on ci.id_cart = c.id
         join user u on c.user_id = u.id
where sop.quantity > 1
# and YEAR(sop.created_at) = YEAR(now())
# and month(sop.created_at) = MONTH(now())
order by sop.created_at desc;

class VirtualMachine:
    def __init__(self):
        self.registers = [0] * 4  # 4 регистра общего назначения
        self.memory = [0] * 256  # Виртуальная память размером 256 байт

    def load_program(self, program):
        address = 0
        for instruction in program:
            self.memory[address] = instruction
            address += 1

    def execute(self):
        pc = 0  # Счетчик команд
        while True:
            print(self.registers)
            opcode = self.memory[pc]
            if opcode == 0:  # Остановка программы
                break
            elif opcode == 1:  # Load
                reg_index = self.memory[pc + 1]
                address = self.memory[pc + 2]
                self.registers[reg_index] = self.memory[address]
                pc += 3
            elif opcode == 2:  # Write
                reg_index = self.memory[pc + 1]
                address = self.memory[pc + 2]
                self.memory[address] = self.registers[reg_index]
                pc += 3
            elif opcode == 3:  # Addition
                reg_index = self.memory[pc + 1]
                reg_index1 = self.memory[pc + 2]
                reg_index2 = self.memory[pc + 3]
                self.registers[reg_index] = self.registers[reg_index1] + self.registers[reg_index2]
                pc += 4
            else:
                print(f"Unknown opcode: {opcode}")
                break

# Пример программы в виде десятичного кода
program = [
    1, 0, 10,   # Загрузить значение из адреса 10 в регистр 0
    1, 1, 20,   # Загрузить значение из адреса 20 в регистр 1
    3, 2, 0, 1,  # Сложить значения из регистров 0 и 1 и сохранить результат в регистр 2
    2, 2, 30,   # Сохранить значение из регистра 2 в адрес 30
    0          # Остановка программы
]


vm = VirtualMachine()
vm.load_program(program)

# Выполняем
vm.execute()

# Выводим результат из памяти
print(vm.memory[30])

Modem = peripheral.find('modem',rednet.open)

--Replace with actual account db
AccountDetails = {
    admin = "admin"
}
IncomingRequests = {}
rednet.host("AmaZincServer", "Main")

while true do
    local eventData = {os.pullEvent()}
    local event = eventData[1]
    if event == "rednet_message" then
        local id, message
        event, id, message = unpack(eventData)
        if(message.type == "login") then
            local username = message.username
            local password = message.password
            local pasGet = AccountDetails[username]
            if pasGet == nil then
                rednet.send(id, {type="loginError", message="Incorrect Username!"}, "login")
            elseif password ~= pasGet then
                rednet.send(id, {type="loginError", message="Incorrect Password!"}, "login")
            else
                rednet.send(id, {type="loginSuccess", message="Neat!"}, "login")
            end
        end
            
       end
    end
